in what situations does a mlb pitcher earn a save erica apparently you don't watch it that religiously rule of the rules of baseball the official scorer shall credit a pitcher with a save when such pitcher meets all four of the following conditions a he is the finishing pitcher in a game won by his team b he is not the winning pitcher c he is credited with at least a third of an inning pitched and d he satisfies one of the following conditions he enters the game with a lead of no more than three runs and pitches for at least one inning he enters the game regardless of the count with the potential tying run either on base or at bat or on deck that is the potential tying run is either already on base or is one of the first two batters he faces or he pitches for at least three innings Save (sport) Baseball Baseball statistics Softball 1919 World Series Pedro Mart__nez Pitcher Detroit Tigers Toronto Blue Jays Roger Clemens St. Louis Cardinals Win (baseball) 2004 American League Championship Series Andr__s Galarraga Hank Aaron International League Baseball Stars Sandy Koufax Starting pitcher World Series Grover Cleveland Alexander Nolan Ryan Stolen base Chicago Cubs Chicago White Sox Earned run average Closer (baseball) New York Mets Baseball scorekeeping Don Newcombe October 4 in baseball Firpo Marberry Box score (baseball) Tris Speaker Early Wynn San Francisco Giants Atlanta Braves Home run 1986 World Series Perfect game Batting average Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim Pete Rose October 20 in baseball October 13 in baseball New York Yankees October 16 in baseball 1987 National League Championship Series October 22 in baseball Joaqu__n And__jar Montr__al Expos Don Drysdale Bunt Mariano Rivera 2001 World Series Randy Johnson Eric Gagne 1987 World Series 1986 National League Championship Series Ty Cobb Luis Tiant Los Angeles Dodgers Interference (baseball) Yankees-Red Sox Rivalry November 3 in baseball October 10 in baseball October 5 in baseball Washington Nationals October